eated_at":"2023-01-18T16:24:30Z","updated_at":"2023-01-18T16:24:30Z","body":"Per [RFC 6265 #6.1](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6265#section-6.1):\r\n\r\n> General-use user agents SHOULD\r\n   provide each of the following minimum capabilities:\r\n>\r\n> - At least 4096 bytes per cookie (as measured by the sum of the length of the cookie's name, value, and attributes).\r\n> - At least 50 cookies per domain.\r\n> - At least 3000 cookies total.\r\n\r\nWe can't reliably know how many cookies there are per domain, since a request for `/foo` will omit any cookies that have `Path=/bar`, though we _could_ warn if we know there are _at least_ 50 cookies and we try to set a new one. Warning on individual cookies is definitely the easier win though.\r\n\r\nShould it be a warning or an error? In production you _probably_ don't want a request to fail because of an outsize cookie, since not all cookies are essential. But in development you probably do want that. So maybe it's just a dev-time error?","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/comments/1387345141/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Rich-Harris","id":1162160,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNjIxNjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1162160?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris","html_url":"https://github.com/Rich-Harris","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/orgs","repos_url