-Harris/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-01-18T23:48:04Z","updated_at":"2023-01-18T23:57:05Z","body":"I've just tested this in Chrome and Firefox (edit: and Safari):\r\n\r\n```js\r\n/** @type {import('@sveltejs/kit').Handle} */\r\nexport function handle({ event, resolve }) {\r\n  console.log(`small.length ${event.cookies.get('small')?.length}`);\r\n  console.log(`large.length ${event.cookies.get('large')?.length}`);\r\n\r\n  event.cookies.set('small', 'a'.repeat(3000), { path: '/' });\r\n  event.cookies.set('large', 'a'.repeat(5000), { path: '/' });\r\n\r\n  return resolve(event);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter the initial load, both report the same thing:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsmall.length 3000\r\nlarge.length undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe large cookie is simply discarded — which is potentially very bad — so I'm strongly of the view that this should be an error rather than a warning. Though oddly the limit in all three browsers appears to be 4,129 bytes (for the whole thing — attributes and value) rather than 4,096.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/comments/1396242293/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Rich-Harris","id":1162160,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNjIxNjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1162160?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris","html_url":"https://github.com/Rich-Harris","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.c